This script is a command-line interface (CLI) tool built using standard Python libraries to interact with a local API running at http://localhost:8000, allowing users to register to the system, log in, view their profile information, create new runs, and list their past runs; additionally, the authorization token received after logging in is saved to the .cli_token file in the local directory and is automatically used in the background for other commands that require authorization.

Register
python cli.py register <name> <email> <password>

Log in
python cli.py login <name> <password>

View your profile
python cli.py me

Submit a new run
python cli.py create-run <run_type> "input data"
run_type is default=cloud fn

View your past runs
python cli.py runs

